external_knowledge:
Sailing the smoothest waters: In the metaphorical context, it refers to the developers whose games have the best performance (highest ranking scores) and the least disruptions (lowest penalties).;
Average ranking score: Represents the mean performance score given to games by players.;
Total penalties: Represents the cumulative penalties incurred in gameplay, indicating smoother sails mean fewer penalties.

sql:
SELECT AVG(avg_lap_time) AS average_lap_time
FROM submissions
WHERE tournament_id = 0;

SELECT user_id, AVG(avg_lap_time) AS average_lap_time
FROM submissions
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT submission_id, avg_lap_time
FROM submissions
ORDER BY avg_lap_time DESC;

SELECT COUNT(s.submission_id) AS total_submissions
FROM submissions s
JOIN leaderboards l ON s.submission_id = l.submission_id;

SELECT submission_time
FROM submissions
ORDER BY submission_time DESC;

SELECT AVG(avg_lap_time) AS average_lap_time
FROM submissions
WHERE user_id = '1' AND tournament_id = 1;

SELECT submission_time
FROM submissions
WHERE submission_id = 1;

SELECT alias
FROM users
WHERE user_id = '0';

external_knowledge:
- 'championship event' refers to tournament with ID 1;
- 'top five racers based on their overall race duration' means the users with the highest total lap time across all their laps;
- 'average lap times' refers to the average lap time per user;

sql:
SELECT user_id, avg_lap_time
FROM submissions
WHERE avg_lap_time > (SELECT AVG(avg_lap_time) FROM submissions);

external_knowledge:
- "confirmed accounts" refers to users with a verification_status of 1;
- "first competition" refers to the tournament with tournament_id 1;
- "considered quite high" means an average ranking score greater than 50,000.

- Experienced competitors: Users with more than 5 entries in the tournament;
- Latest event: The tournament with the most recent start date;
- Showing consistent performance: Average leaderboard score >= 100;
- Typical lap time: Average of each user's lap times.

sql:
SELECT MAX(ranking_score) 
FROM leaderboards 
WHERE tournament_id = (SELECT tournament_id FROM tournaments WHERE tournament_name = 'Grand Prix 2022');

SELECT AVG(ranking_score) AS average_ranking_score
FROM leaderboards
WHERE tournament_id = 1;

SELECT AVG(penalties) AS average_penalties
FROM submissions
WHERE feedback IS NOT NULL AND feedback != '';
